title: Ranking the Stars
overview: Ranking the Stars is a television program from presented by Paul de Leeuw in which 10 famous people receive questions that have been asked by a panel of 'ordinary citizens'. On the basis of the questions, the celebrities must rank themselves and their fellow candidates: in between one to ten in ranking to try and mach what the ordinary Dutch people have allocated to them. Every participant placed on the correct number delivers one point. The person (or those) who gets the most points in one broadcast wins the relevant episode and receives a prize!
